  "texts": [
    "For example, for HSBC (Table 5), the MSE values of Informer, TFT, and Dual Transformer are closely aligned when using fewer related firms.",
    "In addition to the Dual Transformer, both Informer and TFT models show a greater tendency to performance improvement in some cases when polarity scores are added as input (Table 3, 7, and 10).",
    "This indicates that models with a self-attention mechanism, such as Informer and TFT, are better equipped to capture the intercompany relationships that influence stock prices.N-Beats, while not consistently outperforming attention-based models, shows relatively strong performance in scenarios without polarity scores (e.g., Table 5 and 10), suggesting its effectiveness in capturing temporal dependencies purely from price history.",
    "However, its inability to utilize polarity-based information limits its flexibility in multi-source feature integration compared to Transformer-based approaches.For LSTM, TCN, SVR, and Random Forest, adding polarity scores on top of historical close prices generally does not improve prediction(a) Apple (b) Airbus (c) HSBC (d) Infusystem (e) Tencent (f) Toyota (a) Pepsi (b) Petrobras Generally, in this experimental setup, the proposed Dual Transformer model exhibits state-ofthe-art performance in forecasting stock prices by effectively leveraging the polarity of related firms.",
    "Additionally, the results highlight the importance of intercompany relationships and advanced Transformer-based architectures in financial prediction tasks."
  ],
